An: Sky god, head of the Anunnaki.
Enlil: God of wind, air, earth, and storms.
balaj: A type of drum used in Sumerian music.
Anuna: A group of deities in Sumerian mythology.
Suen: Another name for the moon god Nanna.
En-hedu-ana: Ancient Sumerian high priestess and poet.
Lugal-ane: A ruler mentioned in Sumerian texts.
Acimbabbar: Another name for the moon god Nanna.
E-ana: Temple dedicated to the goddess Inana.
Ucumgal-ana: A deity mentioned in Sumerian texts.
Ecdam-kug: A shrine mentioned in Sumerian texts.
Ningal: Wife of the moon god Nanna.
